00039 public:
00040         /*
00041          * This subclass represents simple structure
00042          * to store animated frame data: cached pixmap, and next frame delay.
00043          *
00044          * It provides copyconstructor, wich makes possible to simple
00045          * assign two containers with this classes.
00046          *
00047          * All data will be duplicated in such case.
00048          */
00049         class FrameInfo {
00050         public:
00051                 QPixmap *pixmap; //frame pixmap
00052                 uint delay; //next frame delay
00053 
00054                 FrameInfo(QPixmap *_pixmap, uint _delay) {
00055                         pixmap = _pixmap;
00056                         delay = _delay;
00057                 }
00058 
00059                 FrameInfo(const FrameInfo& source) {
00060                         pixmap = source.pixmap;
00061                         delay = source.delay;
00062                 }
00063 
00064                 void detach() {
00065                         pixmap = new QPixmap(*pixmap);
00066                 }
00067         };
00068 
00069         /*
00070          * This helper class represents data structure
00071          * for storing frames.
00072          *
00073          * It adds references counter and
00074          * mutex, to provide thread-safety.
00075          */
00076         class Data: public QList<FrameInfo> {
00077         public:
00078                 uint     refs;    //references count
00079                 QSize    size;    //size of the pixmaps
00080                 QString  file;    //just to speedup the cache
00081                 bool     resized;
00082 
00083                 Data(QString szFile) :
00084                         QList<FrameInfo> (), refs(0), file(szFile), resized(false) {
00085                 }
00086 
00087                 Data(Data& other) :
00088                         QList<FrameInfo> (other), refs(0), file(other.file), resized(false) {
00089                                 for(int i=0;i<count();i++)
00090                                 {
00091                                         this->operator [](i).detach();
00092                                 }
00093                 }
00094         };
